On March 18, the Goverment of the Brcko District of Bosnia and Herzegovina announced the prohibition to work with economic operators engaged in trade. Exceptions are made regarding:

a) filling stations in accordance with the prescribed working hours, and a ban on the part of the filling station in which the catering activity is performed ;

b) trade in food and consumer goods (hygiene and personal hygiene products, etc.) by 6:00 pm;

c) trade of food and consumer goods (hygiene and personal hygiene products, etc.) within the shopping malls by 6:00 pm;

d) Trade in protective equipment by 6:00 pm.

- Undertakings which are prohibited from engaging in a commercial activity that provide goods for the required activities which are permitted to work in accordance with this Order may apply to the Crisis Staff for approval of the delivery of goods.

